I"Ê<p><a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/pupil-light-response-stabilizes-luminance-on-retina">Pupil size has traditionally been seen as a low-level reflex in response to light</a>. However, it turns out that a wide range of high-level cognitive factors can modulate the changes in pupil size. Among those factors are cognitive load and <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/visual-imagery-brightness-modulates-pupil-size">visual imagery</a>.</p>
